<div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
	<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Apply to become an academy privacy notice</h1>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		The Department for Education (DfE) owns the Apply to become an academy service. 
		It is the <LINK></LINK> Data Controller (external website) for any information the service collects.
		This notice explains how we use that data.
	</p>

	<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">What data we collect</h3>
	<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
		<li>school headteacher details including their name, email address and phone number</li>
		<li>governing body details including the name of the chair, their email address and their phone number</li>
	</ul>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		We also use the <LINK></LINK> DfE Sign-in service to capture the name, role and email address of the application’s author.
	</p>
	
	<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Why we use it</h3>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		We capture this data so that we can:
	</p>
	<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
		<li>consider a school's application to become an academy</li>
		<li>coordinate teams involved in the conversion process</li>
		<li>contact you about your application</li>
		<li>invite people to take part in user research</li>
		<li>get feedback on the service</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Who we share your data with</h3>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		Please read these Terms of Use (“General Terms”) carefully before using this service (the “Service”).
	</p>

	<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">How long we keep your data</h3>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		We will hold your data for 6 years.
	</p>

	<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Our legal basis</h3>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		<LINK></LINK>The law (external website) says that we can use the data you provide to:
	</p>
	<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
		<li>perform a public task as part of our function as a department</li>
	</ul>

	<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Your rights</h3>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		By law you are entitled to:
	</p>
	<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
		<li>ask to see a copy of any information we hold about you - this is called a Subject Access Request (SAR)</li>
		<li>ask us to correct mistakes in your data</li>
		<li>ask us to stop processing it</li>
		<li>ask us to delete it</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		If you ask us to delete or stop processing data from an ongoing application, we may not be able to continue with it.
	</p>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		You may also want to:
	</p>
	<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
		<li><LINK></LINK>read the DfE’s Personal Information Charter for more information on the data it holds, and how to make an SAR</li>
		<li><LINK></LINK>visit the Information Commissioner’s Office website to learn more about your rights</li>
	</ul>

	<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Contact us or make a complaint</h3>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		If you have any questions about the way we use your data, or if you want to make a complaint, you can:
	</p>
	<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
		<li><LINK></LINK>use the DfE contact form, or</li>
		<li>write to our Data Protection Officer (DPO)</li>
	</ul>

	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		Data Protection Officer
		Department for Education
		Piccadilly Gate
		Store Street
		Manchester
		M1 2WD
	</p>

	<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Changes to this policy</h3>
	<p class="govuk-body-l">
		We recommend that you come back to this page from time to time as we sometimes need to update this information.
		Last updated 2 August 2022
	</p>

</div>
